{"timestamp": "2025-12-02 20:33:06.121307", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submission recorded.\n\nSummary of submission:\n- is_anomaly: true\n- faulty_devices: [\"server_access_router\"]\n- root_cause_name: [\"ospf_area_misconfiguration\"]\n\nRationale: The backend 20.200.0.0/24 is locally present but not advertised into the global OSPF domain (missing from core/distribution routing tables). This points to the server-access router (where the backend and public server nets connect) not redistributing/advertising the backend subnet — consistent with an OSPF advertisement/area/configuration issue.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 2470, "output_tokens": 117, "total_tokens": 2587, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 1664}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
